97 SECTION 4.
98 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 31-7-153, relating to standards for
99 patient care and agency operation, regulations as to issuance, denial, suspension, or
100 revocation of licenses, and hearings, as follows:
101 "31-7-153.
102 The department shall promulgate regulations which define standards for the care, treatment,
103 health, safety, welfare, and comfort of patients served by home health agencies and for the
104 maintenance and operation of home health agencies which will promote safe and adequate
105 care and treatment of the patients. These regulations shall be no less stringent than those
106 required for participation of home health agencies in the Title XVIII medicare Medicare
107 program and shall include, but not be limited to, a provision requiring the agency to have
108 policies established by a professional group which includes at least one physician and one
109 registered nurse and appropriate representation from other professional disciplines;
110 provisions governing the services the agency provides; provisions for the supervision of
111 services by a physician, advanced practice registered nurse, physician assistant, or
112 registered nurse, as appropriate, and maintenance of clinical records on all patients,
113 including a plan of treatment prescribed by a physician. The department is authorized to
114 issue, deny, suspend, or revoke licenses in accordance with regulations promulgated
